[TextResourceContents(uri=AnyUrl('knowledge://domain/docs/current%20debates%20around%20open-source%20vs%20closed-source%20AI%20evaluate%20trade-offs%20recommend%20which%20approach%20is%20better%20for%20long-term%20AI%20safety'), mimeType='text/plain', meta=None, text="[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Open vs Closed Source]\nA hybrid approach - open weights with restricted fine-tuning APIs - is emerging as a practical middle ground for safety-conscious deployment.\n\n[SECTION | AI Safety / Open vs Closed Source]\nSection 'Open vs Closed Source' in domain 'AI Safety': Open-source AI models promote transparency and allow the research community to audit weights, training data, and inference code. | Closed-source AI systems give organisations tighter control over misuse but reduce external accountability and peer review.\n\n[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Open vs Closed Source]\nOpen-source AI models promote transparency and allow the research community to audit weights, training data, and inference code.\n\n[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Open vs Closed Source]\nClosed-source AI systems give organisations tighter control over misuse but reduce external accountability and peer review.\n\n[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Open vs Closed Source]\nThe EU AI Act treats open-source foundation models differently from closed proprietary ones, applying lighter obligations to the former.\n\n[SENTENCE | LLM Regulation / Government Approaches]\nThe US Executive Order on AI (Oct 2023) requires dual-use foundation model developers to share safety test results with the government.\n\n[SENTENCE | LLM Regulation / Industry Self-Regulation]\nFrontier AI companies including Anthropic, Google DeepMind, and OpenAI signed voluntary safety commitments at the UK AI Safety Summit (2023).\n\n[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Alignment Techniques]\nConstitutional AI (CAI) uses a set of principles to guide self-critique and revision, reducing reliance on human labellers.\n\n[SENTENCE | AI Safety / Alignment Techniques]\nScalable oversight research investigates how humans can supervise AI systems that are smarter than themselves.")]
